   <text>
      <body>
         <cell style="font-size: 11pt;">Says his last letter contained a letter from Erpenius as well as a letter to Bloem. Received Tengnagels last writing in the meantime, which included a lot of big talk from Bloem. Do not want to hear it - want him to immediately pay his whole debt and demand his house in the city and his country house as colleteral. Says he is unsure about the value of the 'assignation on Brandenburg', want to get a recommendation from the arch duke Alberto (has a connection via good friends). Does not know what effects the war will have on his business, which makes it important to act soon and solidify position. Ends the letter saying he's praying for something (not sure) to be of consolation to 'us catholics'. Attached letter on 195r: Describes current affairs. A potential marriage between the "English Son" and the "Spanish Daughter". Arminians have been quiet since the degree against them was issued. No preparations for war with the end of the Dutch-Spanish truce in sight. States General are debating whether to send fleet to the West Indies or to keep it at home just in case of war (one of these is desired by the 'common man', not sure which). Heard that there were rumours in Brabant that the Hollanders would come and siege Antwerp. Proved false, but shows that Brabant should be alert.</cell>
      </body>
